{"word":"ἀποσβέννυμι","slug":"ἀποσβέννυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποσβέννυμι</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to put out, extinguish, quench</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> aor2 and <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a>, and aor1 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>— <i>to be extinguished, go out, cease to exist</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}